com.xilinx.rapidwright.device

Class Device

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.xilinx.rapidwright.device.Device
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable

    public class Device
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.io.Serializable
    This is the main class that stores information about each Xilinx part. It contains a 2D grid of Tiles which contain all the routing and sites necessary for a placer and router.
    Author:
    Chris Lavin Created on: Apr 22, 2010
    See Also:

        Returns:

      • emptySingletonDeviceMap

        public static void emptySingletonDeviceMap()
        Clears the singleton map, thus deleting any references to the device objects. If the user of the API deletes all references to the device objects, this will enable the garbage collector to remove the devices from memory.

      • getCorrespondingSite

        public static Site getCorrespondingSite(Site current,
                                        SiteTypeEnum type,
                                        Tile newSiteTile)
        A method to get the corresponding primitive site for current in a different tile. For example in a Virtex 4, there are 4 slices in a CLB tile, when moving a hard macro the current slice must go in the same spot in a new CLB tile

        current - The current primitive site of the instance.
        newSiteTile - The tile of the new proposed site.
        Returns:
        The corresponding site in tile newSite, or null if no corresponding site exists.

      • getExactFamilyType

        public FamilyType getExactFamilyType()
        Gets and returns the all lower case exact Xilinx family type for this device (ex: qvirtex4 instead of virtex4). DO NOT use exact family methods if it is to be used for accessing device or wire enumeration files as RapidWright does not generate files for devices that have XDLRC compatible files.
        Returns:
        The exact Xilinx family type for this device.

      • getArchitecture

        public FamilyType getArchitecture()

        Returns:
        The base family type of the part for this device.

      • getSiteIndex

        public java.util.ArrayList<Site[]> getSiteIndex()
        This method will get (create if null) a data structure which stores all of the device's primitive sites by type. To get all of the primitive sites of a particular type, use the SiteTypeEnum.ordinal() method to get the representative integer and use that value to index into the ArrayList. This will return an array of all primitive sites of that same type.
        Returns:
        The data structure which stores all of the primitive sites separated by type.

      • getCompatibleSiteIndex

        public java.util.ArrayList<Site[]> getCompatibleSiteIndex()
        This method will get (create if null) a data structure which stores all of the compatible sites for each site type. To get all the compatible sites of a particular type, use the SiteTypeEnum.ordinal() method to get the representative integer and use that value to index into the ArrayList. This will return an array of all compatible sites of that same type.
        Returns:
        The data structure which stores all compatible sites for each type.

      • getAllCompatibleSites

        public Site[] getAllCompatibleSites(SiteTypeEnum type)
        This method will get all compatible sites for a particular site type in this device. For example, a SLICEL can be placed at all SLICEL sites AND all SLICEM sites. If the type given were SLICEL, this method would return an array of all SLICEL and SLICEM sites.
        Parameters:
        type - The type for which to find compatible sites.
        Returns:
        An array of compatible sites suitable for placement of a site of type type.
